CHAPTER III
INTERMEDIARIES
Approval. . Any recognised entity or entities desirous of operating in IFSC as an intermediary, may form a

company to provide such financial services relating to securities market, as permitted by the Board.
Nature of clients. .( ) Any intermediary permitted by the Board for operating within the IFSC shall provide financial
services to the following categories of clients:
(i) a person not resident in India;
(ii) a non-resident Indian;
(iii) a financial institution resident in India who is eligible under FEMA to invest funds
offshore, to the extent of outward investment permitted;

